Maximise your recovery:

Habit Physiotherapy and Rehabilitation Clinics have met the stringent requirements of the Physiotherapy Accreditation Scheme which results in you receiving simply the best Physiotherapy treatment available. As a contracted ACC provider we can register your injury directly with ACC, saving you time and money. A doctors referral is not necessary.

ACC co-payment is only $20 for standard physiotherapy treatment (initial and follow up sessions). An additional surcharge may apply for extended treatment sessions.

Opening hours:
Monday – Thursday: 7:30am to 6:00pm
Friday: 7:30am-5:00pm
Saturday: 9:00am-12:00pm (Evans Bay and Petone only)

Our Physiotherapists are trained in the most effective and safe techniques for the treatment of all injuries. We offer many treatment alternatives and will implement the most appropriate option for you and your injury. Habit Physiotherapy patients experience complete body balance as a result of adequate rehabilitation, injury prevention education and sound training advice and programming.

At Habit Physiotherapy we strive to have an understanding of each client\'s needs and goals, closely following individual\'s progress to ensure that each person is rehabilitated to their maximum potential, often surpassing their pre injury level of flexibility and wellbeing.

Services:

• Sports Injuries
• Back and Neck Injuries
• Exercise Based Rehabilitation
• Workplace Assessment and Injury Treatment
• Posture and Muscle Balance
• Assessment
• Post Op/Fracture Rehabilitation
• Corporate Health Solutions
• Advanced Exercise Programming
• Workplace Solutions

You no longer need a doctors referral to be covered by ACC. We can register your injury with ACC directly, minimizing the cost to you and maximizing the speed of your recovery.

As required we can also refer you for x-ray or specialist consultation.

Cashman Physiotherapy was founded 20 years ago on The Terrace by Rob Cashman specialising in Sports and Spinal therapy.

As well as Rob Cashman we have three other very experience staff, Loralee Reid, Alistair Fergus and Liam MacLachlan, who between them can cater for any type of injury you may have; we have large, private treatment rooms and the best selection of magazines in town though as we endeavour to see our clients at their appointment time, the chances of you being able to read them are somewhat slim.

Half an hour is allocated for an initial assessment and generally 15 minute for any further appointments and our clinic is open Monday to Friday from 7.30 through to 5 pm.

For pricing please refer to our website www.cashmanphysio.co.nz

Clinics opening hours

Mon-Fri 8:00 am to 5:00 pm

Saturday clinics by appointment only

Northcross Physiotherapy and Rehabilitation is situated on Aucklands North Shore in the Northcross Specialist Centre at 950 East Coast Rd, Northcross. The fully air-conditioned building is shared with a dentist and an orthodontist. Access to the premises is via entrances on both East Coast Road and Oteha Valley Road. There are a total of twenty parking spaces including two for disabled persons. The car park is linked to that of the neighbouring Shore Care Facility allowing for over-flow of parking to and from each of the neighbouring premises.
